caption: Accidentally ordered take-out from Chicago Curry House when they were closed and our order got routed here instead, which I'm actually happy with. It was a super pleasant experience from the courtesy phone call letting me know my mistake to picking up and chatting with one of the employees. However, the best part was the food was absolutely delicious. No knock to Curry House, but I think the dishes from here tasted a notch better overall. The tandoori chicken was so moist and flavorful as opposed to overcooked dryness that you get sometimes. The same came be said for the chicken curry. It was like the dishes were stewed at the perfect time just for my order. In the future, I will absolutely make a point to order from this location. 9/10 portions to price
My favorite Nepalese/Indian restaurant. The flavors are rich and the spicy dishes are truly spicy! I especially love the lamb dishes and the lamb samosas!

Received a coupon in the mail for 25% off and no way to use the discount online. In the store he refused to honor the coupon the did not expire until December. I did receive a 15% discount but this is just a fraud. Don’t send out coupons if you won’t honor them. Very disappointed and angry.

While traveling I always look for a good Indian restaurant. In Chicago, that restaurant is Nepal House. The Chicken Chili Masala is fantastic. Great flavor and a spicy kick. Delivery is fast and the food is piping hot.

Honestly my favorite local restaurant. I stumbled upon Chicago Curry House about a year ago and haven’t stopped coming by since! I was thrilled when I found out they were still doing take out and delivery out of the Nepal House on Michigan. Do yourself a favor and stop by. Everything has such a consistent depth of flavor and the portions are just what you want AND need.
I like it here always quality food & service. I will be back with my friends. The place has a nice atmosphere.
Amazing food- so tasty and authentic. My significant other has two intense food allergies, and they were able to accommodate his needs and make food from scratch! So thankful to have tasty food

The worst indian food I have eaten in the US. We ordered 5 different items totaling $80 for takeout. The starter was chilli potato which was basically big whole undercooked potatoes seasoned only in the surface. Burnt naan bread, raw tomato puree paneer curry and inedible noodles. When we called to complain all we were told was feedback will be given to chef and the call was cut with no attempt to apologise let alone offer recompensation of any kind for the food. One of the first time I have thrown away almost untouched food entirely.
GREAT FOOD ITS REALLY TASTIER

Great food and great portions! Got take out for a group of friends and we all tried different dishes. They were all delicious. I had the Chicken Korma and I could not recommend it enough (especially if you have a low spice tolerance like me). Also, the garlic naan and lamb samosas were to die for. It's a little pricey but absolutely worth it.

My friend and I were looking for a replacement for our hometown Indiana Indian buffet and I would definitely come back here to eat again. Cost about $30 for two buffet dinners and a cup of chai. I preferred the curries, samosas, pakora and vegetables (paneer and chana masala) to some of the meat items (goat and chicken Tikka).

We had a taste for Indian food and this place had good reviews so we decided to give this place a go! They had the lunch buffet going on so thats what we went with. My favorite was the butter chicken and tandori chicken. The butter chicken was amazing, thinking about the taste is making my mouth water right now. Their mango pudding was also very delicious, I had about 2 bowls. The rice pudding was lacking some flavor. They are suppose to be know for the Momo dumplings but we were too full to order. Next time I would love to try the momo dumplings and would probably do a la carte instead of the buffet. The servers were nice and constantly came over to refill our waters. Cannot wait to come back! After that, no one checked in to see if we needed anything while we were eating. Then once we wanted to leave, we waiting at the check out counter for awhile again before anyone could help us pay for the meal. Charging for sauces like Raita while many other restaurants serve it as complimentary.  Staff & Service - quite unprofessional. The staff seemed all over the place, not very well organized. There was another customer who had placed his order for pickup an hour before he got there and still had to wait for his food. The employee was justifying why the order was late rather than providing exceptional customer service. When we got there we noticed the restroom did not have any hand soap and a broken towel dispenser - we saw multiple employees use the restroom and continue to serve and go back in the kitchen.  The restaurant could use professional management and employ best practices across the board to make it a much better experience for customers.
